episodes.title: Chapter One: MADMAX
episodes.description: As the town preps for Halloween, a high-scoring rival shakes things up at the arcade, and a skeptical Hopper inspects a field of rotting pumpkins.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: Trick or Treat, Freak
episodes.description: After Will sees something terrible on trick-or-treat night, Mike wonders whether Eleven's still out there. Nancy wrestles with the truth about Barb.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: The Pollywog
episodes.description: Dustin adopts a strange new pet, and Eleven grows increasingly impatient. A well-meaning Bob urges Will to stand up to his fears.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: Will the Wise
episodes.description: An ailing Will opens up to Joyce -- with disturbing results. While Hopper digs for the truth, Eleven unearths a surprising discovery.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: Dig Dug
episodes.description: Nancy and Jonathan swap conspiracy theories with a new ally as Eleven searches for someone from her past. “Bob the Brain” tackles a difficult problem.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: The Spy
episodes.description: Will's connection to a shadowy evil grows stronger, but no one's quite sure how to stop it. Elsewhere, Dustin and Steve forge an unlikely bond.

episodes.title: Chapter One: The Vanishing of Will Byers
episodes.description: On his way home from a friend's house, young Will sees something terrifying. Nearby, a sinister secret lurks in the depths of a government lab.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: The Weirdo on Maple Street
episodes.description: Lucas, Mike and Dustin try to talk to the girl they found in the woods. Hopper questions an anxious Joyce about an unsettling phone call.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: Holly, Jolly
episodes.description: An increasingly concerned Nancy looks for Barb and finds out what Jonathan's been up to. Joyce is convinced Will is trying to talk to her.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: The Body
episodes.description: Refusing to believe Will is dead, Joyce tries to connect with her son. The boys give Eleven a makeover. Nancy and Jonathan form an unlikely alliance.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: The Flea and the Acrobat
episodes.description: Hopper breaks into the lab while Nancy and Jonathan confront the force that took Will. The boys ask Mr. Clarke how to travel to another dimension.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: The Monster
episodes.description: A frantic Jonathan looks for Nancy in the darkness, but Steve's looking for her, too. Hopper and Joyce uncover the truth about the lab's experiments.

episodes.title: Chapter Seven: The Bathtub
episodes.description: Eleven struggles to reach Will, while Lucas warns that "the bad men are coming." Nancy and Jonathan show the police what Jonathan caught on camera.

episodes.title: Chapter Eight: The Upside Down
episodes.description: Dr. Brenner holds Hopper and Joyce for questioning while the boys wait with Eleven in the gym. Back at Will's, Nancy and Jonathan prepare for battle.

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: When an unassuming high school chemistry teacher discovers he has a rare form of lung cancer, he decides to team up with a former student and create a top of the line crystal meth in a used RV, to provide for his family once he is gone.

episodes.title: Cat's in the Bag...
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse attempt to tie up loose ends. The desperate situation gets more complicated with the flip of a coin. Walt's wife, Skyler, becomes suspicious of Walt's strange behavior.

episodes.title: ...And the Bag's in the River
episodes.description: Walter fights with Jesse over his drug use, causing him to leave Walter alone with their captive, Krazy-8. Meanwhile, Hank has a scared straight moment with Walter Jr. after his aunt discovers he has been smoking pot. Also, Skylar is upset when Walter stays away from home.

episodes.title: Cancer Man
episodes.description: Walter finally tells his family that he has been stricken with cancer. Meanwhile, the DEA believes Albuquerque has a new, big time player to worry about. Meanwhile, a worthy recipient is the target of a depressed Walter's anger, and Jesse makes a surprise visit to his parents home.

episodes.title: Gray Matter
episodes.description: Walter and Skyler attend a former colleague's party. Jesse tries to free himself from the drugs, while Skyler organizes an intervention.

episodes.title: Crazy Handful of Nothin'
episodes.description: The side effects of chemo begin to plague Walt. Meanwhile, the DEA rounds up suspected dealers.

episodes.title: A No Rough Stuff Type Deal
episodes.description: Walter accepts his new identity as a drug dealer after a PTA meeting. Elsewhere, Jesse decides to put his aunt's house on the market and Skyler is the recipient of a baby shower.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: In this exciting episode of Breaking Bad, the story continues to unfold with unexpected twists and turns that will keep you on the edge of your seat.

episodes.title: Seven Thirty-Seven
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse are vividly reminded of Tuco’s volatile nature, and try to figure a way out of their business partnership. Hank attempts to mend fences between the estranged Marie and Skyler.

episodes.title: Grilled
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse find themselves in close quarters with an unhinged Tuco. Marie and Hank comfort Skyler, who is distraught over Walt’s disappearance. Hank pays a visit to Mrs. Pinkman on some not-so-official business.

episodes.title: Bit by a Dead Bee
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse become short on cash when they try to cover their tracks. Meanwhile, the DEA has a lead that could them straight to Walt and Jesse.

episodes.title: Down
episodes.description: Walt attempts to reconnect with his family, while Jesse struggles to rebuild his life.

episodes.title: Breakage
episodes.description: Hank suffers from the aftermath of his encounter with Tuco. Meanwhile, Jesse hires a crew to get their product out on the streets.

episodes.title: Peekaboo
episodes.description: Walt's secret is in jeopardy when Skyler thanks Gretchen for paying for his treatment.

episodes.title: Wolferton Splash
episodes.description: A young Princess Elizabeth marries Prince Philip. As King George VI’s health worsens, Winston Churchill is elected prime minister for the second time.

episodes.title: Hyde Park Corner
episodes.description: With King George too ill to travel, Elizabeth and Philip embark on a four-continent Commonwealth tour. Party leaders attempt to undermine Churchill.

episodes.title: Windsor
episodes.description: With Elizabeth in a new role, Philip tries to assert some power. Churchill wants to delay the coronation. King George’s disgraced brother arrives.

episodes.title: Act of God
episodes.description: When dense smog cripples London for days and creates a serious health hazard, Churchill’s inaction leaves him vulnerable to his political enemies.

episodes.title: Smoke and Mirrors
episodes.description: Elizabeth rejects protocol by appointing Philip to coordinate her coronation, but his ideas create conflict. The Duke of Windsor returns to London.

episodes.title: Gelignite
episodes.description: Margaret and Peter come to Elizabeth with a request. With a royal scandal about to break in the newspapers, the Queen Mother intervenes.

episodes.title: Scientia Potentia Est
episodes.description: As the Soviets test the H-bomb, both Churchill and Eden have major health crises. Angry about her inadequate education, Elizabeth hires a tutor.

episodes.title: Pride & Joy
episodes.description: Elizabeth and Philip go on an exhausting world journey. Margaret takes over some of her sister’s official duties and tries to liven things up.

episodes.title: Misadventure
episodes.description: As Philip leaves for a long tour, Elizabeth makes an upsetting discovery. Prime Minister Eden wants to strike back after Egypt seizes the Suez Canal.

episodes.title: A Company of Men
episodes.description: Elizabeth feels disconnected from Philip. Eden copes with international pressure and ill health. An interview stirs up harrowing memories for Philip.

episodes.title: Lisbon
episodes.description: Palace insiders try to prevent a scandal that could reflect poorly on Philip. Eden faces censure from his cabinet and the press.

episodes.title: Beryl
episodes.description: When Elizabeth and Philip throw a grand party for their 10th anniversary, both Margaret and the new Prime Minister experience romantic tribulations.

episodes.title: Marionettes
episodes.description: After Elizabeth makes a tone-deaf speech at a Jaguar factory, she and the monarchy come under public attack from an outspoken lord.

episodes.title: Vergangenheit
episodes.description: A secret World War II document opens Elizabeth's eyes to grim realities about a family member. The Duke of Windsor campaigns to re-enter public life.

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: A documentary crew arrives at the offices of Dunder Mifflin to observe the employees and learn about modern management. Manager Michael Scott tries to paint a happy picture, while sales rep Jim fights with his nemesis Dwight and flirts with receptionist Pam.

episodes.title: Diversity Day
episodes.description: A consultant arrives to teach the staff about tolerance and diversity but Michael insists on imparting his own knowledge. Meanwhile, Jim struggles to keep hold of a lucrative contract extension.

episodes.title: Health Care
episodes.description: Michael doesn't want to upset the staff so he gets Dwight to pass on news about the company's reduced health provisions. Fed up with his nosiness, Jim and Pam pretend they are suffering from a variety of conditions including Ebola, Mad Cow Disease, spontaneous dentohydroplosion, hotdog fingers, nano-robot infection...

episodes.title: The Alliance
episodes.description: Michael arranges a morale-boosting birthday party for Meredith and is determined to come up with the funniest message in her card. Dwight wants a pact with Jim to fight the downsizing, and Michael regrets showing off when Oscar asks for sponsorship for a charity walk being undertaken by his nephew, who has cerebral palsy.

episodes.title: Basketball
episodes.description: The office staff play a basketball game against the warehouse workers in which Jim shows off to impress Pam and upstage her fiancee who is on the opposing team.

episodes.title: Hot Girl
episodes.description: A woman who comes to the office to sell purses gets the male members of staff excited. She rejects Dwight's advances, but Michael reckons he's still in with a chance.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: In this exciting episode of The Office, the story continues to unfold with unexpected twists and turns that will keep you on the edge of your seat.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: In this exciting episode of The Office, the story continues to unfold with unexpected twists and turns that will keep you on the edge of your seat.

episodes.title: The Dundies
episodes.description: It's time for the "Dundies", Dunder Mifflin's annual awards banquet (held at the neighborhood Chili's), and the staff must endure the excruciating performance of their inept emcee, boss Michael Scott.

episodes.title: Sexual Harassment
episodes.description: Just as corporate tells Toby, one of the workers at the Scranton branch, to give a seminar on sexual harassment issues, Michael receives a visit from his obnoxious sales-rep friend Todd Packer.  The two chauvinistic friends try to prove that the office is not in need of harassment counseling, but only wind up making the situation worse, causing yet another zany day at the office.

episodes.title: Office Olympics
episodes.description: While Michael and Dwight are out of the office for the day trying to close a deal on a new condo for Michael, Jim and Pam arrange for the staff to participate in an "Office Olympics," where the workers play strange, invented games (among them, Dunderball, Hate Ball...and Pam Pong) that they usually play while the boss is out.  At the end of the day, the festivities cheer up everyone - even the oblivious Michael.

episodes.title: The Fire
episodes.description: The Office is forced into the parking lot for the day when a fire starts in the kitchen. To ease everyone's boredom, Jim suggests a game of "Desert Island" and "Who Would You Do?", where certain staff members reveal a little too much information about themselves. Throughout the day, Michael talks business with Ryan, leaving Dwight feeling left out.

episodes.title: Halloween
episodes.description: While everyone else in the office enjoys the spooky Halloween festivities and talks about the staff's costumes, Michael ponders who he should fire when the threat of downsizing becomes a reality and his boss orders him to fire one of his staff.  Meanwhile, Jim and Pam put Dwight's resume on job-searching websites, which may make Michael's job a little easier, and Pam encourages Jim to set his goals higher by applying for a better job, which makes Jim consider his friendship with Pam.

episodes.title: The Fight
episodes.description: When Dwight embarrasses Michael by punching him in the stomach at work, Jim organizes a lunchtime rematch at Dwight's Dojo. Meanwhile, Pam becomes annoyed at Jim when he gets too physical with her, Ryan updates the emergency contact information on a secret mission, and Michael tantalizes Ryan when the boss gets a hold of Ryan's cell phone number.

episodes.title: Secrets
episodes.description: In 2019, a local boy's disappearance stokes fear in the residents of Winden, a small German town with a strange and tragic history.

episodes.title: Lies
episodes.description: When a grim discovery leaves the police baffled, Ulrich seeks a search warrant for the power plant. A mysterious stranger checks into the hotel.

episodes.title: Past and Present
episodes.description: It's 1986, and Ulrich's brother, Mads, has been missing for a month. Confusion reigns as past and present intertwine.

episodes.title: Double Lives
episodes.description: Bizarre occurrences give Charlotte a sense of déjà vu, and she suspects Peter is hiding something. Franziska snaps when Magnus confronts her.

episodes.title: Truths
episodes.description: Hannah takes her obsession with Ulrich too far. The stranger asks Regina to deliver an important package. Martha is torn between Jonas and Bartosz.

episodes.title: Sic Mundus Creatus Est
episodes.description: Ulrich looks to the past for answers and dredges up disturbing family secrets. Armed with new tools, Jonas probes the cave's murky depths.

episodes.title: Crossroads
episodes.description: Ulrich questions a frail and frightened Helge in the nursing home. Jonas searches for Mikkel, but the stranger warns him about meddling with the past.

episodes.title: As You Sow, So You Shall Reap
episodes.description: In 1953, the disfigured bodies of two boys are exhumed at a construction site, the future location of Winden's nuclear power plant.

episodes.title: Beginnings and Endings
episodes.description: Six months after the disappearances, the police form a task force. In 2052, Jonas learns that most of Winden perished in an apocalyptic event.

episodes.title: Dark Matter
episodes.description: Clausen and Charlotte interview Regina. The Stranger takes Hannah to 1987, where Claudia has an unnerving encounter and Egon visits an old nemesis.

episodes.title: Ghosts
episodes.description: In 1954, a missing Helge returns, but he'll only speak to Noah. In 1987, Claudia brings the time machine to Tannhaus, and Egon questions Ulrich again.

episodes.title: The Travelers
episodes.description: Jonas meets an ominous figure. While the kids comb the cave for answers, the adults gather in the bunker to share what they know about the travelers.

episodes.title: Lost and Found
episodes.description: In 1987, Ulrich seizes an opportunity. The kids return to the cave with the time machine, and Jonas learns of a loophole that could change the future.

episodes.title: An Endless Cycle
episodes.description: Armed with a plan to prevent the apocalypse, Jonas travels to 2019. During the Nielsens' anniversary party, Ulrich sneaks off with Hannah.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: Birmingham, 1919. Thomas Shelby controls the Peaky Blinders, one of the city's most feared criminal organisations, but his ambitions go beyond running the streets. When a crate of guns goes missing, Thomas recognises an opportunity to move up in the world.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Thomas fixes a horserace, provoking the ire of local kingpin Billy Kimber. He also starts a war with gypsy family the Lees. Meanwhile, Inspector Campbell carries out a vicious raid of Small Heath in search of the stolen guns.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Thomas Shelby plans to go to Cheltenham races in order to get closer to Billy Kimber. Knowing the gangster's appetite for beautiful women, Thomas invites Grace to accompany him. Meanwhile some IRA sympathisers approach Thomas with an offer to buy the stolen guns.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Thomas Shelby's war with the Lee family of gypsies escalates, and Campbell puts further pressure on him to deliver the stolen guns. Meanwhile Thomas's brother John plans to marry a former prostitute, but Thomas suspects that she's still on the game.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Thomas Shelby has to deal with an IRA chief who has come to Small Heath to avenge his cousin's death. Meanwhile Campbell gets closer to the stolen guns, and Grace has to decide whether her loyalties lie with him or with Thomas.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: As Thomas Shelby prepares to oust Billy Kimber, hidden secrets are revealed and the family have to face up to the problems that have divided them. Meanwhile, Campbell, obsessed with taking down the Peaky Blinders, unleashes one last plan to destroy them.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: In this exciting episode of Peaky Blinders, the story continues to unfold with unexpected twists and turns that will keep you on the edge of your seat.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: In this exciting episode of Peaky Blinders, the story continues to unfold with unexpected twists and turns that will keep you on the edge of your seat.

Episode 1
episodes.description: Business is booming for the Peaky Blinders, as Shelby starts expanding both his legal and illegal operations. He plans for the future, looking at managing a race track in the South. He soon comes across some new adversaries, testing him in very different ways. Back in Birmingham, Shelby's home town is challenged by members of his family reacting to the upturn in their fortunes. A enemy from his past also returns hoping to exact their plan of revenge of biblical proportions.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Tommy offers to help Polly by searching for her children, who long ago were taken from her. In London, Tommy risks his life by meeting enigmatic leader Alfie Solomons. Meanwhile Arthur continues to feel the devastating effects of the Great War.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Tommy hatches a plan to take control of the southern racecourses. He also meets the aristocratic May Carleton, and sees an opportunity to move up in the world. Meanwhile both Major Campbell and London gangster Darby Sabini plan Tommy's downfall.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Arthur leads the Peaky Blinders takeover of London's Eden Club. Sabini decides to put old feuds to one side, convincing Alfie to one side to get rid of the Peaky Blinders. Tommy hires May Carleton to train his race horse, and the pair become fast friends. In Birmingham, Michael joins the family firm, hoping to help Tommy's businesses become more legitimate. Whilst Tommy's insecurities are intensified as he discovers what Major Campbell wants him to do.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Arthur and Michael both end up arrested and imprisoned. As Tommy's base in London is obliterated. Major Campbell has Tommy and his family under his thumb. Polly compromises herself hoping to secure Michael's freedom, but their relationship may be beyond repair at this point. Someone from Tommy's past pays him a visit, opening old wounds and leaving him to make a impossible decision.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: As derby day arrives, Tommy is faced with impossible decisions as he plans to strike back at his enemies and take the family business to another level. Meanwhile, Major Campbell has one final card to play - one that he is certain will bring about Tommy's demise.

episodes.description: Thomas Shelby’s wedding day has arrived at last, but while his guests enjoy the celebrations he has important business to conduct, as a mysterious stranger makes their presence known.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.description: Tommy goes to London to meet the wildly eccentric and volatile Duke Leon and soon discovers the extreme lengths his new paymasters are willing to go to in their quest for power. In Birmingham a personal dispute with the Italians threatens to explode into a devastating war.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.description: Responding to the Italians’ actions, Tommy is set on a path of deadly vengeance that could take him to his darkest place yet, and threatens to splinter the family. As Arthur struggles with his conscience, Linda implores him to stop his illicit work with the Peaky Blinders.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.description: Tommy takes his brothers on a hunting expedition and shares some  important family news. He also outlines his intentions for the most  daring criminal act the Peaky Blinders have ever undertaken.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.description: As the Russians test the Peaky Blinders men in their own distinctive and  debauched way, Tommy realises that he is being seriously outmanoeuvred.  Desperate for help, he rekindles a business relationship with a  dangerous former acquaintance.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.description: As Tommy prepares to commit the most audacious crime  of his career, an unexpected blow is struck, putting him under  unbearable pressure. As he faces his worst fears he needs help more than ever, but is increasingly uncertain about whom he can trust. In a nerve-shredding race against time, Tommy is forced to confront  hard truths about himself and his family that could change the Peaky  Blinders forever.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.description: December 1925. When Tommy receives a mysterious letter on Christmas Eve, he realises that the Shelbys are in danger of annihilation.
episodes.title: The Noose

episodes.description: As the Shelbys come to terms with the shocking events of Christmas Day, Tommy endeavours to unite his family and a bold new enemy makes his move.
episodes.title: Heathens

episodes.description: Tradition weighs upon Arthur as Changretta finds a chink in the Shelby armour and Changretta continues to plan ways to continue the vendetta in the most devastating way possible.
episodes.title: Blackbird

episodes.description: The Peaky Blinders are lured by the Italians into a cat-and-mouse chase on the streets of Birmingham.  As his factory lies idle, Tommy confronts the possibility that the Communists might win and he will be deemed a traitor to his class.
episodes.title: Dangerous

episodes.description: Tommy finds himself engaged in bloody battle with Luca Changretta and his gang. Lizzie has even greater news to break. Meanwhile, an army colonel has questions for Ada about her past as a communist, and Jessie Eden confirms just how far she is prepared to go in pursuit of her cause.
episodes.title: The Duel

episodes.description: It is the night of the big fight - Bonnie Gold versus Goliath. But as the bell rings and the crowd goes wild, dangers lurk in the shadows for Tommy Shelby and his family. When Changretta plays his final ace, he sets in motion a series of events that will change the Peaky Blinders forever.
episodes.title: The Company

episodes.description: 1929 – While his family deals with the repercussions of the Wall Street Crash, Tommy Shelby MP faces new dangers from unexpected quarters.
episodes.title: Black Tuesday

episodes.description: The Peaky Blinders come under fire when Tommy finds danger on his doorstep and a friend is brutally attacked. Could there be a traitor in the Shelby family’s midst?
episodes.title: Black Cats

episodes.description: As the charismatic Mosley shows his hand, Tommy prepares to make a treacherous new alliance.
episodes.title: Strategy

episodes.description: Tommy agrees to dangerous new partnerships when a golden opportunity presents itself, and a Shelby party promises fireworks.
episodes.title: The Loop

episodes.description: As Tommy reveals his intentions for Mosley, someone close to the Shelbys is targeted.
episodes.title: The Shock

episodes.description: News of Tommy's activities have reached Winston Churchill. At a family meeting, Tommy lays out his plans for Mosley, which will take place at a rally Sir Oswald is leading. Tommy is surprised by another strategy, coming from an unexpected corner. Meanwhile, Tommy has his own secrets to reveal.
episodes.title: Mr. Jones

episodes.description: Tommy sets off to North America, where the end of Prohibition brings new opportunities. But he faces new danger from an old adversary who is finally making his move.
episodes.title: Black Day

episodes.description: Tommy gets involved in a power game with fascists, freedom fighters and Boston gangsters. As the players plan to double cross him, Tommy visits an old ally in Camden.
episodes.title: Black Shirt

episodes.description: Faced with devastating news, Tommy goes on a quest to discover who it was that placed a curse on his family. In Birmingham, Ada takes charge, and Arthur takes on some new recruits.
episodes.title: Gold

episodes.description: Tommy establishes a connection between crime and political power that could alter the course of history. He also receives life-changing news from an unexpected source.
episodes.title: Sapphire

episodes.description: In the light of extraordinary personal revelations, Tommy takes a course of action that will change everything. Meanwhile, his enemies’ plans start to fall into place.
episodes.title: The Road to Hell

episodes.description: As the clouds of the coming storm gather, Tommy Shelby faces the consequences of his experiences and his actions.
episodes.title: Lock and Key
Descenso
episodes.description: Chilean drug chemist Cockroach brings his product to Colombian smuggler Pablo Escobar. DEA agent Steve Murphy joins the war on drugs in Bogota.

episodes.title: The Sword of Simón Bolívar
episodes.description: Communist radical group M-19 makes a move against the narcos, while Murphy gets an education in Colombian law enforcement from his new partner Peña.

episodes.title: The Men of Always
episodes.description: Murphy encounters the depths of government corruption when he and Peña try to derail Escobar's political ambitions by proving he's a narco.

episodes.title: The Palace in Flames
episodes.description: Despite a new extradition treaty, the U.S. puts more money into fighting communism, creating new challenges for Murphy and Peña in the hunt for Pablo.

episodes.title: There Will Be a Future
episodes.description: Pablo's extreme methods put the narcos on the brink of war with Carillo and  the government. Peña tries to protect his witness, Elisa.

episodes.title: Explosivos
episodes.description: Peña and Carillo close in on Gacha, while Murphy tries to protect pro-extradition candidate Gaviria from a notorious assassin connected to Pablo.

episodes.title: You Will Cry Tears of Blood
episodes.description: Pablo goes into hiding as the political tide turns against him, but he finds a way to strike back. Murphy and Peña finally get the CIA to help them.

episodes.title: La Gran Mentira
episodes.description: A tragic mistake forces the government to change tactics in the fight against Pablo. But Pablo faces bigger threats from inside his empire.

episodes.title: Free at Last
episodes.description: In the aftermath of a massive military effort to take Pablo into custody, the family reunites while enemies worry. Steve and Connie fight about safety.

episodes.title: Cambalache
episodes.description: Tata gets impatient with life on the run. Pablo responds to President Gaviria's reward offer. Steve and Javier meet their new boss.

episodes.title: Our Man in Madrid
episodes.description: President Gaviria has a new job for an old colleague. The Search Bloc's new tactics shake up Pablo, but also unsettle Steve and Javier.

episodes.title: The Good, The Bad, and The Dead
episodes.description: The Cali cartel discusses moving in on Pablo's territory. Limón proposes a plan to Maritza. Tata gets a gun for protection.

episodes.title: The Enemies of My Enemy
episodes.description: The Search Bloc gets a new leader. Javier loses faith in the system. Pablo brings Tata's brother Carlos down from Miami to cheer her up.

episodes.title: Los Pepes
episodes.description: The newly-formed Los Pepes want to destroy Pablo and his empire. Tata's brother urges her to leave and seek safety with her children.

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: An introduction to the gang. After Rachel leaves her fiancé at the altar, she moves in with Monica and finds that independence is not so easy, particularly without Daddy's credit cards.

episodes.title: The One with the Sonogram at the End
episodes.description: Ross's lesbian ex-wife, Carol, is pregnant with his child, and he doesn't like her choice of last name for the baby. Rachel finds out that her ex-fiancé went on what would have been their honeymoon with her maid of honor.

episodes.title: The One with the Thumb
episodes.description: Monica finds it difficult to break up with her latest boyfriend whom everyone likes; Chandler is reunited with his beloved cigarettes; Phoebe receives a large sum of money.

episodes.title: The One with George Stephanopoulos
episodes.description: While the men attend a hockey game and end up at a hospital, a delivery man accidentally brings a pizza meant for George Stephanopoulos, who lives across the street from the girls; they decide to peek at the former White House advisor with their binoculars.

episodes.title: The One with the East German Laundry Detergent
episodes.description: While Chandler and Phoebe decide to break up with their significant others on the same night, Ross helps Rachel do laundry and considers the evening a first date. Joey has Monica pose as his new girlfriend, because he wants to get back with the girl he just dumped.

episodes.title: The One with the Butt
episodes.description: Joey gets his big film break when he's hired to be Al Pacino's stunt butt. Ross tries to be less conservative and Chandler thinks his fantasies have come true when he has an affair with a married woman.

episodes.title: The One with the Blackout
episodes.description: A power outage leaves Chandler stranded in an ATM vestibule with Victoria's Secret model Jill Goodacre, whom he desperately tries to impress, Ross tries to ask Rachel out on a date, and Joey learns that Monica used to be infatuated with him.

episodes.title: The One Where Nana Dies Twice
episodes.description: Monica and Ross mourn the death of their grandmother with a little help from the gang, and Monica and her mom come to an unspoken understanding about the relationship between mothers and daughters. Meanwhile, Chandler is irritated by office speculation that he is gay.

episodes.title: The One with Ross's New Girlfriend
episodes.description: Rachel waits patiently at the airport for Ross, returning from China. Meanwhile, after giving Joey and Chandler new haircuts, Phoebe is persuaded to cut Monica's hair. And Joey learns that his tailor is a very naughty man.

episodes.title: The One with the Breast Milk
episodes.description: The guys are uncomfortable with the thought of Carol's breast milk while Rachel is upset by Monica's growing friendship with Julie. Meanwhile, Joey competes with a fellow cologne spritzer for the affections of a beautiful colleague.

episodes.title: The One Where Heckles Dies
episodes.description: After Mr. Heckles dies and leaves all his belongings to Monica and Rachel, Chandler discovers eerie similarities between the late eccentric man and his own life. Ross and Phoebe have a dispute over the progression of evolution.

episodes.title: The One with Phoebe's Husband
episodes.description: The gang is amazed to learn that Phoebe married a gay Canadian ice dancer to help him get his green card. And Ross seeks relationship advice from Rachel.

episodes.title: The One with Five Steaks and an Eggplant
episodes.description: When a sexy woman calls the wrong number, Chandler seeks to make the most of the situation. Income issues divide the friends; Monica, Ross and Chandler have money, while Phoebe, Rachel and Joey don't.

episodes.title: The One with the Baby on the Bus
episodes.description: Chandler and Joey lose Ross's son, Ben, while checking out women on a bus. Phoebe loses her Central Perk singing gig to a professional singer. And Ross has an allergic reaction to Monica's kiwi-lime pie.

episodes.title: Winter Is Coming
episodes.description: Jon Arryn, the Hand of the King, is dead. King Robert Baratheon plans to ask his oldest friend, Eddard Stark, to take Jon's place. Across the sea, Viserys Targaryen plans to wed his sister to a nomadic warlord in exchange for an army.

episodes.title: The Kingsroad
episodes.description: While Bran recovers from his fall, Ned takes only his daughters to Kings Landing. Jon Snow goes with his uncle Benjen to The Wall. Tyrion joins them.

episodes.title: Lord Snow
episodes.description: Lord Stark and his daughters arrive at King's Landing to discover the intrigues of the king's realm.

episodes.title: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
episodes.description: Eddard investigates Jon Arryn's murder. Jon befriends Samwell Tarly, a coward who has come to join the Night's Watch.

episodes.title: The Wolf and the Lion
episodes.description: Catelyn has captured Tyrion and plans to bring him to her sister, Lysa Arryn, at The Vale, to be tried for his, supposed, crimes against Bran. Robert plans to have Daenerys killed, but Eddard refuses to be a part of it and quits.

episodes.title: A Golden Crown
episodes.description: While recovering from his battle with Jamie, Eddard is forced to run the kingdom while Robert goes hunting. Tyrion demands a trial by combat for his freedom. Viserys is losing his patience with Drogo.

episodes.title: You Win or You Die
episodes.description: Robert has been injured while hunting and is dying. Jon and the others finally take their vows to the Night's Watch. A man, sent by Robert, is captured for trying to poison Daenerys. Furious, Drogo vows to attack the Seven Kingdoms.

episodes.title: The Pointy End
episodes.description: Eddard and his men are betrayed and captured by the Lannisters. When word reaches Robb, he plans to go to war to rescue them. The White Walkers attack The Wall. Tyrion returns to his father with some new friends.

episodes.title: Baelor
episodes.description: Robb goes to war against the Lannisters. Jon finds himself struggling on deciding if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Drogo has fallen ill from a fresh battle wound. Daenerys is desperate to save him.

episodes.title: Fire and Blood
episodes.description: With Ned dead, Robb vows to get revenge on the Lannisters. Jon must officially decide if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Daenerys says her final goodbye to Drogo.

episodes.title: The North Remembers
episodes.description: As Robb Stark and his northern army continue the war against the Lannisters, Tyrion arrives in King’s Landing to counsel Joffrey and temper the young king’s excesses.  On the island of Dragonstone, Stannis Baratheon plots an invasion to claim his late brother’s throne, allying himself with the fiery Melisandre, a strange priestess of a stranger god.  Across the sea, Daenerys, her three young dragons, and the khalasar trek through the Red Waste in search of allies, or water.  In the North, Bran presides over a threadbare Winterfell, while beyond the Wall, Jon Snow and the Night’s Watch must shelter with a devious wildling.

episodes.title: The Night Lands
episodes.description: In the wake of a bloody purge in the capital, Tyrion chastens Cersei for alienating the king’s subjects.  On the road north, Arya shares a secret with Gendry, a Night’s Watch recruit.  With supplies dwindling, one of Dany’s scouts returns with news of their position.  After nine years as a Stark ward, Theon Greyjoy reunites with his father Balon, who wants to restore the ancient Kingdom of the Iron Islands.  Davos enlists Salladhor Saan, a pirate, to join forces with Stannis and Melisandre for a naval invasion of King’s Landing.

episodes.title: What is Dead May Never Die
episodes.description: At the Red Keep, Tyrion plots three alliances through the promise of marriage.  Catelyn arrives in the Stormlands to forge an alliance of her own, but King Renly, his new wife Margaery, and her brother Loras Tyrell have other plans.  At Winterfell, Luwin tries to decipher Bran’s dreams.

episodes.title: Garden of Bones
episodes.description: Joffrey punishes Sansa for Robb’s victories, and Tyrion scrambles to temper the king’s cruelty. Catelyn entreats Stannis and Renly to unite against the Lannisters. Dany and her khalasar arrive at the prosperous city of Qarth. Tyrion coerces a relative into being his eyes and ears. Arya and Gendry are taken to Harrenhal, where their lives are in the hands of Ser Gregor Clegane. Stannis orders Davos to smuggle Melisandre into a secret cove.

episodes.title: The Ghost of Harrenhal
episodes.description: The Baratheon rivalry ends, driving Catelyn to flee and Littlefinger to act. At King’s Landing, Tyrion’s source alerts him to Joffrey’s defense plan - and a mysterious secret weapon. Theon sails to the Stony Shore to prove he’s worthy to be called Ironborn. At Harrenhal, Arya receives a promise from Jaqen H’ghar, one of the prisoners she saved from the Gold Cloaks. The Night’s Watch arrive at the Fist of the First Men, an ancient ringfort where they hope to stem the wildings' advance.

episodes.title: The Old Gods and the New
episodes.description: Theon seizes control of Winterfell. Jon captures a wildling, named Ygritte and is given a chance to prove himself. At King's Landing, after the Lannisters send Myrcella off to be married, the people begin to turn against King Joffrey. Arya comes face to face with a surprise visitor. Daenerys looks to buy ships to sail for the Seven Kingdoms.

episodes.title: A Man Without Honor
episodes.description: Jamie meets a distant relative. Daenerys receives an invitation to the House of the Undying. Theon leads a search party. Jon loses his way in the wilderness. Cersei counsels Sansa.

episodes.title: The Prince of Winterfell
episodes.description: Betrayal befalls Robb. Jon and Qhorin are taken prisoner by the wildlings. Theon receives a visitor at Winterfell and must make an important decision. Meanwhile, Stannis is just days away from reaching King's Landing and Tyrion prepares for his arrival. At Harrenhal, Arya, Gendry and Hot Pie plan their escape.

episodes.title: Blackwater
episodes.description: Tyrion and the Lannisters fight for their lives as Stannis’ fleet assaults King’s Landing.

episodes.title: Valar Morghulis
episodes.description: Tyrion awakens to a changed situation. King Joffrey doles out rewards to his subjects. As Theon stirs his men to action, Luwin offers some final advice. Brienne silences Jaime. Arya receives a gift from Jaqen. Dany goes to a strange place. Jon proves himself to Qhorin.

episodes.title: Valar Dohaeris
episodes.description: Jon meets the King-Beyond-the-Wall while his Night Watch Brothers flee south. In King's Landing, Tyrion wants a reward, Margaery shows her charitable nature, Cersei arranges a dinner party, and Littlefinger offers to help Sansa. Across the Narrow Sea, Daenerys starts her journey west.

episodes.title: Dark Wings, Dark Words
episodes.description: Sansa says too much. Shae asks Tyrion for a favor. Jaime finds a way to pass the time, while Arya encounters the Brotherhood Without Banners.

episodes.title: Walk of Punishment
episodes.description: Tyrion shoulders new responsibilities. Jon is taken to the Fist of the First Men. Daenerys meets with the slavers. Jaime strikes a deal with his captors.

episodes.title: And Now His Watch Is Ended
episodes.description: Trouble brews among the Night's Watch at Craster's. Margaery takes Joffrey out of his comfort zone. Arya meets the leader of the Brotherhood. Varys plots revenge on an old foe. Theon mournfully recalls his missteps. Daenerys deftly orchestrates her exit from Astapor.

episodes.title: Kissed by Fire
episodes.description: The Hound is judged by the gods. Jaime is judged by men. Jon proves himself. Robb is betrayed. Tyrion learns the cost of weddings.

episodes.title: The Climb
episodes.description: Tywin plans strategic unions for the Lannisters. Melisandre pays a visit to the Riverlands. Robb weighs a compromise to repair his alliance with House Frey. Roose Bolton decides what to do with Jaime Lannister. Jon, Ygritte, and the Wildlings face a daunting climb.

episodes.title: The Bear and the Maiden Fair
episodes.description: Daenerys exchanges gifts with a slave lord outside of Yunkai. As Sansa frets about her prospects, Shae chafes at Tyrion’s new situation. Tywin counsels the king, and Melisandre reveals a secret to Gendry. Brienne faces a formidable foe in Harrenhal.

episodes.title: Second Sons
episodes.description: King’s Landing hosts a wedding, and Tyrion and Sansa spend the night together. Daenerys tries to persuade the Second Sons to join her against Yunkai. Stannis releases Davos from the dungeons. Sam and Gilly meet an older gentleman.

episodes.title: The Rains of Castamere
episodes.description: The Lannisters send their regards.

episodes.title: Mhysa
episodes.description: Bran and company travel beyond the Wall. Sam returns to Castle Black. Jon says goodbye to Ygritte. Jaime returns to King's Landing. The Night's Watch asks for help from Stannis. Daenerys waits to see if she is a conqueror or a liberator.

episodes.title: Two Swords
episodes.description: Tyrion welcomes a guest to King’s Landing. At Castle Black, Jon Snow finds himself unwelcome. Dany is pointed to Meereen, the mother of all slave cities. Arya runs into an old friend.

episodes.title: The Lion and the Rose

episodes.title: Lawless Law Firm
episodes.description: Bong Sang Pil is known as the gangster lawyer. He is known to fight with his fist and the law. After hearing news that Cha Moon Sook was appointed as judge for the retrial of the murder of the mayor of Giseong, Lee Young Soo, Sang Pil decides to return to his hometown for the first time in 18 years. Meanwhile, Ha Jae I punches a judge for a wrongful verdict. She ends up getting suspended and returns home after getting fired from her law firm.

episodes.title: The Hearing
episodes.description: After returning to Kiseong, Sang Pil takes over the office that his mother, a civil rights lawyer, used to use. He keeps busy trying to get the chance to defend Hyung Man for the murder of Kiseong's Mayor, Lee Young Soo. Jae I begins to wonder why Sang Pil is so determined to work on this case. She begins to look into it to find out. The day of the hearing is finally here, and Jae I faces danger on her way to the courthouse. Will Sang Pil go to rescue her?

episodes.title: I’m Going to be Arrested Today
episodes.description: After saving Jae I, Sang Pil and Jae I arrive at the courthouse. Sang Pil reveals a shocking truth that changes the conditions of the trial. However, Sang Pil ends up getting arrested for disrupting the trial. While Sang Pil is in prison, Jae I begins to look into the truth behind Mayor Lee Young Soo's murder case. Jae I begins to see Sang Pil in a different light. Meanwhile, Sang Pil agonizes over how to tell Jae I the truth about her mother.

episodes.title: Prove It to Me
episodes.description: Sang Pil devises a plan to ruin An Oh Ju's chances of becoming mayor. Jae I begins to get suspicious of Sang Pil as he seems to be going overboard. She wonders why he seems to be targeting Moon Sook and Oh Ju for no reason. She goes to visit Hyung Man in prison and finds out a shocking truth. Meanwhile, Moon Sook attends an event for the unveiling of her father's statue at Kiseong District Court.

episodes.title: I Came Here For A Reason
episodes.description: Sang Pil and Moon Sook face each other after revealing who they are. Sang Pil tells Moon Sook that he will see this case through. However, Moon Sook is not affected by his declaration. Jae I sees the two of them talking and is shocked to hear the truth. She has a hard time believing what she saw and starts to look into Moon Sook on her own. Sang Pil feels bad about Jae I and keeps an eye on her. Jae I finally finds out the truth about what happened 18 years, but it ends up causing her more trouble.

episodes.title: I’ll Keep Your Promise
episodes.description: Sang Pil tells Jae I about the true face of Moon Sook. Sang Pil and Jae I work together to prove Young Man is not guilty of murdering the mayor Lee Young Soo. Young Man finds out Jae I is Hyun Joo’s daughter. Yeon Hee asks Moon Sook for forgiveness.

episodes.title: Wake Up
episodes.description: Oh Ju has finally accomplished his old desire. He starts to begin the Golden City redevelopment project. Meanwhile, he tries to take revenge on Hyung Man, who puts him in trouble. Sang Pil and Jae I try to stop Oh Ju from doing so. Sang Pil and Jae I versus Moon Sook and Oh Ju begins now.

episodes.title: Hold On
episodes.description: Jae I runs into Hyun Joo, her mother, in 18 years, but doesn’t recognize her. Dae Woong finds out that Hyun Joo has moved back to Kiseong, so he decides to move to Kiseong to meet Oh Ju. Meanwhile, due to Sang Pil's action, Oh Ju fails to keep his shares, so he decides to revenge on Sang Pil in a cruel way.

episodes.title: Fighting from the Inside Out
episodes.description: Sang Pil, who succumbs to Mayor An’s evil plot, now faces murder charges for Dae Woong’s death. Sang Pil and his supporters all fight to prove Sang Pil’s innocence but face unexpected circumstances in court that keeps Attorney Ha on her toes. To make matters worse, Sang Pil is confronted by an old acquaintance that puts him fighting for his life.

episodes.title: Keep Your Enemies Close
episodes.description: Jae I is torn to see her love, Sang Pil, sustain injuries and visits him frequently at the hospital. Sang Pil again faces adversaries and fights to see Jae I one more time. The war between the oppressor and the oppressed deepens while new alliances form. The trial for the murder of Choi Dae Woong continues with the most unpredicted witness taking the stand.

episodes.title: New Alliances
episodes.description: Sang Pil is acquitted of murder at Mayor An’s shocking testimony. Sang Pil is released with all charges dismissed and regroups with the Lawless Law Firm to carry on with his revenge. Meanwhile, Judge Cha’s acceptance of chief justice causes Nam Soon Ja, Judge Cha’s personal secretary, to worry about her daughter’s future. Judge Cha faces the onslaught of the media when an anonymously sent picture with her surfaces; possibly putting her in connection with the disappearance of Han Cheol Kyu, the union president of the Golden City Project.

episodes.title: Wars are Fought with Swords
episodes.description: After sustaining an attack from a defendant’s father, whose son was sentenced to death, Judge Cha slips out of the media’s suspicions regarding the photo. Meanwhile, Bong Sang Pil finds out the true identity of Mama and does not share it with Jae I. Bong Sang Pil finds crucial evidence linking Mayor An to the Choi Dae Woong murder case and uses it put Mayor An in quite the predicament.

episodes.title: Play Your Cards When You Can
episodes.description: Bong Sang Pil now knows who had sent him the notebook and who is playing what hand. He uses this knowledge and devises a plan to ruin Judge Cha’s escape and save Jae I’s mother from murder. Overnight, Mayor An becomes the main suspect in Choi Dae Woong’s murder case due to Gwan Dong’s recorded message and looks to team up with Jae I to bury the past. Meanwhile, Jae I is still upset with Bong Sang Pil for not telling her about her mother and unforgivingly pursues her mother’s whereabouts without him.

episodes.title: I Want to Make a Deal with You
episodes.description: Thanks to Sang Pil’s efforts, Jae I and her father are reunited with her mother after 18 years. Sang Pil’s final plan to bring down Chan Sook goes into effect. Soon Ja is arrested and facing trial when she realizes that Chan Sook has cut her loose. She gets a tempting offer from Sang Pil. Meanwhile, Oh Ju, who is on the run, faces off with Sang Pil after abducting Jae I.

episodes.title: Loyalty Means Nothing
episodes.description: An Oh Ju, who is still being chased by the police, kidnaps Jae I to draw Sang Pil to him. Sang Pil rushes to Jae I and confronts An Oh Ju with vengeance but not without a plan to win him over for his end game. Things heat up in the trial for the murder of the Thai accupressurist as Judge Cha sits as the presiding judge. The defendant, Nam Soon Ja, looks to Sang Pil and Jae I to show their skills as lawyers to bail her out of her predicament, but ultimately, it is her testimony that will determine her fate.

episodes.title: The Final Testimony
episodes.description: In the trial against Nam Soon Ja, Bong Sang Pil and Ha Jae I work together to finalize their revenge where the unthinkable takes place. New witnesses and evidence emerge as Judge Cha squirms to get free of any accusations thrown by the “lawless” couple. Judge Cha does all she can to remove those who can testify against her in and out of the courtroom—including Nam Soon Ja. But is that enough? At the turning point of the trial, Nam Soon Ja agonizes over choosing the right side that will determine her fate and the fate of her daughter.

episodes.description: Dimple struggles to focus but later finds inspiration. Anmol and Vinny spar over his past. Rith uses artificial intelligence to aid his transition.

episodes.title: Hello, Future Wife!
episodes.description: An impromptu engagement party sparks happiness and confusion. Celina learns of a major hack, while a remorseful Anmol tries to make amends.

episodes.title: Beginning, Middle and...
episodes.description: At Technovate in Mumbai, the launch of Betterverse hits a glitch. The couples face emotional decisions over their futures — together and apart.

episodes.title: Thodi Struggle, Bahut Hustle
episodes.description: Abhijeet, a small-town boy with big dreams, leaves behind Delhi and his modest family for a high-paying job in Mumbai. But between five-star hotels, cutthroat colleagues, and fragile friendships, he learns that survival isn't about playing fair - it's about playing smart. In a city built on ambition, will he lose himself before he finds success?

episodes.title: Roti, Kapda Aur Bathtub Wala Makaan
episodes.description: A week into Fusion Funds and the interns are already facing a work life imbalance. They only have a week to find a house. Tired of staying in small spaces, Abhijeet coerces Saurav to be his flatmate so that they can afford a fancy house. he is even willing to go illegal, but competition always catches up.

episodes.title: Jaisa Dikhunga Waise Bikunga
episodes.description: Abhijeet tries to fit into Mumbai's fast world - new house, new style, new rules. But a clash with a colleague and a tough reality check force him to question if changing on the outside is enough to survive inside. In a city that only rewards the polished, Abhijeet realises the real race has just begun.

episodes.title: Dating Radius: 2 KM
episodes.description: Haunted by an old heartbreak, Abhijeet tries to build the perfect life - dream house, dream date, dream image - even hosting a house party to impress. But when a small lie spirals out of control, he's forced to face a harder truth: some lies don't stay small for long.

episodes.title: Bosses From Hell
episodes.description: Old wounds push Abhijeet and Garima to question the small lies we tell to survive. As friendships crack and hidden games come to light, they must decide: in chasing success, what part of themselves are they willing to lose?

episodes.title: Pehli Kamai Pehla Kand
episodes.description: Abhijeet's first paycheck brings celebration, freedom, and a taste of the life he always dreamed of. But as the high wears off, he and his friends are reminded - some moments lift you higher than ever before, only to change everything the next second.

episodes.title: D Se Dosti, D Se Dhokha
episodes.description: Abhijeet's need to prove himself pushes him to make a selfish move - and it costs him more than he imagined. As friendships shatter and regrets build, he's left facing a brutal truth: in chasing success, sometimes you end up standing alone.

episodes.title: Alladin Ka Credit Card
episodes.description: Ostracised after his selfish move, Abhijeet decides he doesn't need anyone. Chasing validation, he buys his way into a new life with Manisha. But as the nights get louder and the bills heavier, Abhijeet begins to learn - you can fake everything, except feeling less alone.

episodes.title: Internet Wala Love
episodes.description: Abhijeet's dream life starts to crack. As fake friendships slip away and mounting credit card debt closes in, a cruel betrayal forces him to face the truth: you can outrun people, but not the loneliness - or the lies you built around it.

episodes.title: Account Balance: Zero
episodes.description: Crushed by debt, broken friendships, and the threat of losing his home, Abhijeet faces the life he built - and the terrifying question of what's left when it all falls apart.

episodes.title: You're Fired
episodes.description: Abhijeet rebuilds his life from scratch - friendships, trust, and a shot at something real. But when layoffs hit Fusion Funds, he's left fighting for the one thing he can't afford to lose again: a future he finally started believing in.

episodes.title: The Invitation
episodes.description: After news of his death, Dr Viswak Sen's staff reaches out to his long-lost family members, inviting them to his mysterious private island.

episodes.title: Island Recci
episodes.description: Vicky, Viswak's forgotten son, is on a mission to learn about a father he never knew. Will Grandmother Meena shed light on that?

episodes.title: Family Matters
episodes.description: Jhansi's life gets upended. While Nikhila goes missing, Arun is startled to learn shocking details about his son Akash. Will that rage consume him?

episodes.title: Grandma Tales
episodes.description: The revelation about Meena's life with Viswak Sen causes uproar among the family members. She is now face to face with her biggest fear.

episodes.title: Lab Rats
episodes.description: The family members turn against each other with a vengeance. Trapped underground, Nikhila makes a startling discovery about the island.

episodes.title: No One is Safe Here
episodes.description: As Vicky searches for the missing Jhansi, he encounters a strange forest creature. Who will triumph?

episodes.title: Science Matters
episodes.description: The family reunites for dinner, and some startling revelations change their perceptions of each other. Now it's a survival of the fittest.

episodes.title: Mind Bending
episodes.description: The pursuit of science comes at a price. With lives at stake, who will finally triumph? What will happen to the legacy of Dr Viswak Sen?

episodes.title: Hell Hath No Fury Like a Man Wronged!
episodes.description: Ready to settle a score, big shot Abhimanyu Nayak arrives in Goa. Back in the past, Shiva’s reunion with his BFF gang ignites the chapter of love, lies and deceit.

episodes.title: The Vendetta
episodes.description: At the casino, Abhimanyu weighs in on his first move. Flashbacks reveal how a romantic date night draws Shiva into a deadly web as he gets framed for a murder.

episodes.title: Tables Have Turned
episodes.description: The aftereffects of his arrest leave Shiva reeling with frame-ups and betrayals. While Tara wrestles with painful memories of her own, Abhimanyu takes charge at the casino.

episodes.title: My Love Is Not a Lie
episodes.description: With her son Kartik missing, a frail and frightened Tara begins the search.  A look into the past offers Tara’s side of the love story, unveiling disturbing secrets.

episodes.title: D-Day
episodes.description: Armed with the ‘perfect heist’ plan, Michael, JK, and Tara brace for their next moves. Ahead of a charity event, Abhimanyu and Michael get into a heated confrontation.

episodes.title: The Godfather
episodes.description: While Shiva is left grilling in prison, his friends-turned-foes start anew after a successful heist. Amidst the uncertainty, Shiva finds his guiding light in the form of Bhau.

episodes.title: Best Served Cold
episodes.description: Conflicts of the past resurface as Abhimanyu and JK have a man-to-man conversation. Drowned in his sorrows, Shiva has one choice to make: give up or retaliate!

episodes.title: Reincarnation
episodes.description: At Tara’s party, Abhimanyu concocts his plan of action. In the past, Bhau’s orchestrated mayhem offers Shiva a second chance at life - a rebirth!

episodes.title: We Are Family
episodes.description: While Tara grows frantic about Divya’s deteriorating health, Abhimanyu reminisces the sufferings of his loved ones. At the prison, a plot to kill Bhau is set in motion.

episodes.title: A Way Back Home
episodes.description: Tension mounts between JK and the Ranes over reopening Shiva’s case. Back home, Abhimanyu finds solace in his father’s embrace. And now, he is all set for his next move!

episodes.title: Is Love a Trap?
episodes.description: Flashbacks reveal how love becomes a hurdle in Abhimanyu’s plan of vengeance. As he storms into Tara’s life again, the resolution for revenge is clear - one way or another!

episodes.title: The Loophole
episodes.description: Looking for answers, Michael dredges up Abhimanyu’s close associate Rana’s story. While he aims to connect the dots, Abhimanyu forms an unlikely bond with Divya.

episodes.title: Men with a Past!
episodes.description: While Abhimanyu and Rana deal with the ghosts of their past, Divya wrestles with her feelings of love. At the casino, Abhimanyu senses an opportunity to get back at Tara.

episodes.title: Of Lost Love and Vengeance
episodes.description: Tension simmers as Abhimanyu pushes Tara to recall the past wounds. While Gargi senses a conspiracy, Abhimanyu answers a big question: What after revenge?

episodes.title: A Mother's Heart
episodes.description: With Gargi’s arrival at the dinner party, Abhimanyu’s identity is at risk of disclosure. Following his hunch, Michael inches dangerously close to the truth.

episodes.title: Fate Is Blind
episodes.description: Bhau warns Abhimanyu to lay low! JK-Gargi-Abhimanyu’s confrontation at the Rane house dredges up past wounds, new revelations, and changing destinies.

episodes.title: The Gameplan
episodes.description: A crucial intel about Abhimanyu makes JK plot his next moves. Meanwhile, Abhimanyu’s growing bond with Tara and Divya spirals into emotional turmoil.

episodes.title: Show of Power
episodes.description: While Bhau guides Abhimanyu on his next plan of action, JK sets his sights on Abhimanyu’s hotel project. A deadly attack at Tara’s casino puts everyone on edge!

episodes.title: The Night I Met You Again
episodes.description: After the casino attack, JK and Abhimanyu seek shelter at the old-yet-familiar Adda. Broken from within, Tara finds solace in a heart-to-heart talk with Abhimanyu.

episodes.title: Blood Ties
episodes.description: Tara grows increasingly concerned when Michael claims to have killed her father. Back at the Rane house, Abhimanyu reminisces painful memories of the past.

episodes.title: Follow the Commander
episodes.description: Abhimanyu keeps things platonic with Divya while Michael’s quest for the truth intensifies. Keeping Abhimanyu out of the loop, Bhau sets a new plan in motion.

episodes.title: Can I Get Over Her?
episodes.description: JK overlooks Michael’s findings about Abhimanyu. Back at the casino, JK’s revelation about wanting a second child leaves Abhimanyu wrestling with pent-up feelings.

episodes.title: Innocent Love
episodes.description: Michael presses on JK’s insecurity, sowing doubts about Kartik’s biological father. While Divya revels in new-found love, Abhimanyu must reconsider his immoral choices.

episodes.title: Cheaters Will Prosper
episodes.description: DNA findings reveal the truth about Kartik’s parentage, leaving JK on edge. Ready to get back at Tara, Abhimanyu remains persistent about his love trap for Divya.

episodes.title: There Will Be Blood
episodes.description: Using Divya as a pawn, Abhimanyu wrestles with a tough choice - act or retreat. Ahead of the D-day, an unexpected tragedy awaits everyone. And this may ruin it all!

episodes.title: Why Did You Betray Me?
episodes.description: Forging a business partnership with JK and Tara, Abhimanyu makes it clear - the vendetta will continue! Determined to unravel the conspiracy, Mert embarks on a quest of his own.

episodes.title: Don’t Dig Your Own Grave!
episodes.description: Mert’s quest to clear Shiva’s name brings him to the jail, where he discovers a crucial intel. As he gets dangerously close to the truth, Bhau takes matters into his own hands.

episodes.title: Let Me Tell You A Story…
episodes.description: To thwart Mert’s investigation, Bhau orchestrates a calculated move. Tara’s world crumbles after finding a videotape that reveals what unfolded on the night of the bank robbery.

episodes.title: My Love Is A Lie
episodes.description: Hit hard by reality, Tara tries to retrospect and seeks refuge at Gargi’s house. While Michael closes in on Bhau, Abhimanyu clears the truth about his growing closeness to Tara.

episodes.title: My Brother Is A Murderer!
episodes.description: Seizing an opportunity, Abhimanyu manages to create a rift between Tara and JK. Things spiral out of control when Mert publishes an article naming Shiva as the murderer.

episodes.title: The Castle Is Falling
episodes.description: A well-timed strategy helps Abhimanyu sow seeds of mistrust between JK and Michael. As old connections begin to alter, he sets his sights on the next target - Tara.

episodes.title: My Game, My Rules
episodes.description: The old player—RC—rises to power, using the videotape to secure control over JK and Michael. Meanwhile, Abhimanyu puts the final touches on his plan to take over Tara’s casinos!

episodes.title: Your Love Is My Solace
episodes.description: Tara wrestles with her growing feelings for Abhimanyu, unknowingly falling for his trap. The trio—RC, Michael, and JK—reflect on setting a ploy for Abhimanyu.

episodes.title: Will You Die For Your Brother?
episodes.description: Revenge is his only motto! A new threat looms over the Rane house with Pakya’s arrival. The truth about Tara and RC’s relationship makes Abhimanyu reconsider his plan.

episodes.title: It’s a Devil’s World
episodes.description: All the pieces fall into place as Pakya gets his hands on the videotape. But a tragedy befalls, pushing Abhimanyu and everyone to the edge. And this may change it all!

episodes.title: I Embrace Death!
episodes.description: Ready to bury his past once and for all, Abhimanyu declares the death of Shiva. Tension flares as Tara receives an anonymous call—Kartik has been kidnapped!

episodes.title: Time’s Ticking On You
episodes.description: Amid mounting pressure, Bhau assigns JK a critical task to save Kartik. And a trap is laid! JK runs into trouble with the police after getting framed at a crime scene.

episodes.title: Let’s Rewind The Clock
episodes.description: Using Tara as the pawn, Abhimanyu inches closer to put an end to the JK chapter. A tense scene unfolds in the courtroom as Tara testifies against JK. And Karma hits back!

episodes.title: All Eyes On You
episodes.description: The intimate picture of Abhimanyu and Tara makes everything clear. While Michael readies to expose him, Divya’s world comes crashing down. A big setback looms over Abhimanyu!

episodes.title: I Am The Destroyer!
episodes.description: Revelations and regrets surface! Tara wrestles with her past and present choices after a fallout with Divya. At the jail, Abhimanyu confronts JK and reveals it all.

episodes.title: Only Innocents Will Suffer
episodes.description: A sudden tragedy pushes Tara on the edge, while JK faces an unexpected visitor. Abhimanyu proposes marriage to Tara, which hints at a new turning point!

episodes.description: Mishka is trying to live up to her strict boss Aditi’s expectations. Meanwhile, both are struggling to fix their marriages with Abir and Anirban, respectively.

episodes.title: Nemey Jachhey Keno
episodes.description: A super angry Aditi's husband is having fun with another woman. Abir tries to convince Mishka to be the hotwife to the bull of his choice.

episodes.title: Fact or Fantasy
episodes.description: Anirban and Mishka end up in a police station while enjoying themselves behind Abir’s back. Abir's reaction does not match his liberal ways.

episodes.title: Karma is a B**ch
episodes.description: Abir and Aditi start to get closer, making Mishka’s life miserable. On the other hand, Anirban realises his true feelings for Mishka.

episodes.description: Mishka and Aditi confront Abir and Anirban for all the mess in their lives. Will the two mismatched couples finally find what they want?

episodes.title: Double Trouble

episodes.title: Secrets of Batsayana

episodes.title: Adalam-Badalam

episodes.description: Behind the closed doors of the Ashrama, a larger evil lurks. Can the couples solve the mystery?

episodes.title: Psycho Puppy Killer
episodes.description: An incident in the locker room after lights-out leaves Vedant in shock. Gossip spreads across the campus following a gruesome killing. The Old Boys of the batch of 2007 return for their reunion, among them is Adhiraj Jaisingh, who seems to be hiding something.

episodes.title: Shadow Boy
episodes.description: A nightmarish incident in the swimming pool leaves Adhiraj shaken. A mysterious mark reappears. Supriya tries to help Vedant. A shocking encounter in the assembly hall brings back memories of Ninad. The Dean takes a call. The Old Boys bring up the past. Adhiraj makes a connection with Vedant. The Shadow Boy reveals itself and an Old Boy disappears.

episodes.title: If You Make Trouble You Will Be Punished
episodes.description: Vedant teaches his classmate a lesson. Supriya helps Adhiraj find a clue to Ninad. Adhiraj drives to Kotagiri for answers. Instead he faces an unexpected truth that forces him to relive the events of the last day of school. Adhiraj’s guilt is finally revealed. At the ceremony to unveil Dean Vyas’s statue, a horrifying incident leaves the school in shock. Vedant reveals his plan to Adhiraj.

episodes.title: The Boy Who Lives Inside Vedant
episodes.description: Vedant remembers what happened in the Dean’s bungalow the night the puppies were killed. The school is reeling from Suyash’s death. Adhiraj grows more desperate in his search for Ninad. The dark force gripping the school grows stronger as the Old Boys cannot leave the campus. Sarthak knows the truth about Vedant.

episodes.title: No Exit
episodes.description: The Old Boys grow desperate as Police Officer Bedi takes over the investigation into Suyash's death. Sarthak learns his lesson. Supriya takes a questionable call about Vedant that leaves her shaken. As Adhiraj delves deeper into the past, a skirmish between the Old Boys reveals a shocking truth about the last day. A gruesome incident at the construction site uncovers a dark secret.

episodes.title: Hush Little Baby
episodes.description: A shocking discovery rocks the school as the investigation takes a turn. Meanwhile, Supriya takes Vedant to a hospital outside the campus. Her dark past is revealed as she learns the truth about Vedant. Dev faces off against Officer Bedi, while Adhiraj finds an unlikely ally and pieces together the events of the last day. A final confrontation leads to an ominous end.

episodes.title: The Farewell
episodes.description: The campus is in the grips of terror as the truth comes to light and Ninad goes on a terror path of revenge. Officer Bedi receives a mysterious sign. Supriya reels from the horror at the hospital as Vedant is still missing. Adhiraj is a man with a plan, even as Dev makes a run for it. But can he escape his fate?

episodes.title: Facchas
episodes.description: Fresher Devika Kumari leaks a video during a sex-ed night at Matilda House, sparking controversy. Principal Datta advocates open dialogue but faces pressure to rusticate Paro Sarna. First-years Wallika, Devika, Tabassum, Vandana, and Trisha are caught in the chaotic excitement of their first semester as Matilda House faces a crisis it might not survive.

episodes.title: Paro Ki PG Party
episodes.description: To prevent the no-hostel-curfew policy from being reversed by their new Principal Lata Bakshi, Matilda House seniors, led by Paro and Shubhra, campaign against the referendum. Bakshi pushes for the vote to go her way to save Matilda House from the fallout of the "sex-education" incident. Vandana, Tabassum, Trisha and Wallika bond at Paro’s PG party, while Devika feels out of place and leaves.

episodes.title: Bhook Hadtaal
episodes.description: Bakshi’s referendum reverses the curfew, sparking opposition from Matilda House’s stalwart faculty and seniors. The freshers’ lives progress: Vandana moves to a PG, Trisha bonds with Tabassum and pursues hockey to impress Parth. Paro, devastated by Matilda House’s loss, starts a hunger strike. As friendships deepen, tensions rise.

episodes.title: Kuch Ziddi Ladkiyan
episodes.description: As their friendships deepen and they discover each other’s passions, Trisha, Vandana, Wally, Tabby, and Devika unknowingly take steps toward becoming Ziddi Girls. When wealthy socialite Anita Raghani challenges public education, Lata Bakshi surprisingly defends it, clashing with Raghani and Sihag. Meanwhile, Paro and friends secretly plan a performance at Masterpiece to defy Bakshi’s censorship.

episodes.title: Main Darna Nahi Chahti
episodes.description: The hunger strike ends, impacting our freshers. Life picks up: Tabassum lands a brand deal, Trisha focuses on hockey, Vandana faces challenges at Experimanch, Wallika joins Paro’s resistance, and Devika struggles financially. Bakshi offers Devika a scholarship, while urging her to spy on Paro, creating a loyalty conflict. As tensions rise, Devika infiltrates the resistance and must choose a side.

episodes.title: Apne Mann Ki Karungi
episodes.description: Tensions arise at Masterpiece as Paro’s resistance group recruits Devika and Wally, while Devika struggles with spying for Bakshi to keep her scholarship. Vandana is tricked into a shocking stage moment, leading to her suspension. Amidst friendship drama and sporting triumphs, Paro’s secret protest against Bakshi collapses. Vandana disappears, leaving our freshers wondering how to help her.

episodes.title: Kya Sabka First Year Itna Happening Hota Hai?
episodes.description: A faltered plan isn’t a failed plan. Paro and the seniors execute their resistance plan at Masterpiece and expose Raghani and Sihag’s agendas. Chaos erupts as PICA members invade Matilda House and attack Paro. Wallika rallies students for justice, while Devika feels betrayed after losing her scholarship. Bakshi must decide if she can save Matilda House from collapse.

episodes.title: Abhivyakti Ke Khatre
episodes.description: The finale presents Matilda House with its biggest challenge yet -privatisation. Many colleges rally in support of Matilda House, while Bakshi and team work to convince the board. Meanwhile, our facchas fight to protect Wally from Mayank Asthana and his men, strengthening their bond and Bakshi goes from fighting against Matilda House to fighting for it. But will it be enough?

episodes.title: A Runaway Life
episodes.description: Seher flees to Mumbai after a fight with Rana. She crashes an auction in Kamathipura, run by Resham and Habiba. Amid chaos over missing Neeti, Seher seizes her chance to present herself, defying Raju's earlier refusal.

episodes.title: Shadows At Play
episodes.description: Seher saves Neeti from Akram's men but is shot. Baburao wins auction. Dr. Anand treats Seher, warns her to flee. Suraiyya caught escaping village. Quadir bribes Inspector Satpute. Seher's fate hangs in balance.

episodes.title: Hunter And Prey
episodes.description: Akram hunts Seher. Dhananjay tortures Suraiyya for Seher's whereabouts. Baburao meets Ivy in Bangkok, plans to meet Chao Fa. Seher finds ally in Sattar. Raju bribes Inspector Satpute to eliminate Seher.

episodes.title: Tale Of Betrayal
episodes.description: Police raid brothels for Seher. Dhananjay torments Suraiyya as Rana's health worsens. Seher escapes, accidentally kills Gafoor. Champa sells Seher to Habiba. Quadir favors Akram in lane distribution, angering Baburao post-Thailand trip.

episodes.title: Secrets And Chains
episodes.description: Flashback reveals Baburao's rise in Kamathipura. Seher learns Champa sold her. Sattar takes ill Champa to Dr. Anand. Baburao starts massage parlor with Thai girls. Quadir investigates Gafoor's murder. Seher rescues minor children with Sattar and Inspector Prabha's help.

episodes.title: Battle To Survive
episodes.description: Minors' rescue revealed. Akram shoots Gotya, blaming Baburao for Gafoor's death. Dhananjay misinformed of Seher's death. Habiba bailed; Prabha warned. Sattar and Seher fall in love. Baburao claims innocence to Quadir. Seher finds Champa dead.

episodes.title: Memories And Scars
episodes.description: Flashback shows Seher-Champa bond. Seher informs Sattar of Champa's death. Dhananjay's men find Seher's photo. Baburao opens parlor with Ivy. Quadir requests meeting. Sattar shows Seher Mumbai. Seher calls Suraiyya; Dhananjay attacks her mid-call.

episodes.title: The Final Showdown
episodes.description: Dhananjay intercepts Seher's call. Power struggles in Kamathipura intensify. Sattar has accident. Dhananjay kills Raju, seeks Seher. Resham plots against Akram. At cremation, chaos erupts. Season ends with Seher, Akram, and Quadir in armed standoff.

episodes.title: Anhoni
episodes.description: Tara and Hemant are a happy couple whose lives revolve around their daughter, Manasvi. Manasvi, a college student's life, takes a drastic turn when she refuses a proposal from her classmate, Rohit.

episodes.title: Zakham
episodes.description: Rohit and his friends abduct Manasvi. On the other hand, Tara and Hemant start a search for her when she is too late. They are shocked to find Manasvi in an injured state, barely alive and breathing.

episodes.title: Andha Kanoon
episodes.description: Manasvi refuses to file a complaint or fight in court, and Hemant supports her decision. While Tara fears that Manasvi’s name will dragged through the mud, she is hell-bent on seeking justice.

episodes.title: Jaal
episodes.description: Tara begins a secret battle against the four criminals under the guidance of Shubhankar Pandit. Her first target, Rohit, is trapped in a scandal. Soon, Rohit and his cousin Aditya are found dead.

episodes.title: Pratishodh
episodes.description: Tara sees a difference in Manasvi’s behaviour, but her fight becomes difficult when ACP Avinash takes up the case of Rohit’s death. Meanwhile, Vikram confesses to his involvement in the crime.

episodes.title: Chaunauti
episodes.description: Vikram is arrested on the charges of assaulting Manasvi. He takes Varun Joshi’s name, who is the son of a renowned lawyer. Meanwhile, Varun’s father, Jayesh, calls Tara and Hemant for a settlement.

episodes.title: Ant-Yudh
episodes.description: Hemant, Tara and Manasvi decide to go to a faraway place for a weekend. Tara confesses to her involvement in the crimes against Rohit and Aditya. Varun appears at the bungalow for a final showdown.

episodes.title: Rahasya
