episodes.title: JHANDU
episodes.description: A shocking incident at a wedding procession ignites a series of events entangling the lives of two families in the lawless city of Mirzapur.

episodes.title: GOODA
episodes.description: Guddu and Bablu have a life-altering choice to make. Munna gets a lesson in loyalty. A new, diabolical contender for Mirzapur emerges.

episodes.title: WAFADAR
episodes.description: A generation-old rivalry is rekindled.

episodes.title: VIRGINITY
episodes.description: Akhandanand tests the boys' moral fibre, leading them down a path of no return. And Sweety must choose between Munna and Guddu.

episodes.title: BHAUKAL
episodes.description: Guddu and Bablu hatch an ambitious plan to increase the gun trade, but for this, both the cops and criminals of Mirzapur must cooperate.

episodes.title: BARFI
episodes.description: A meeting of the mafia heads of Purvanchal masquerading as a Holi party leads to a fracas' that threatens to transform all equations.

episodes.title: LIONS OF MIRZAPUR
episodes.description: Guddu and Bablu have come into their own in their private and professional lives as gangsters. But is it time for a rethink?

episodes.title: TANDAV
episodes.description: Tempers reach a head between Guddu and Bablu while they're in exile. And it's time for the Mr. Purvanchal contest.

episodes.title: YOGYA
episodes.description: Three generations of Tripathis show the world who they really are.

episodes.title: DHENKUL
episodes.description: The Gorakhpur wedding massacre is a thing of the past for Akhandanand Tripathi. His focus is now on the present - the business and conquering larger territory to remain the King of Mirzapur. Everyone who survived that violent night has come out a different person. Despite horrific memories, they know that survival is their only option.

episodes.title: KHARGOSH
episodes.description: The Tripathis, still unaware that Guddu and Golu are alive, continue to form new alliances. Munna impresses Bauji and Akhandanand with the way he has handled a negotiation. Akhandanand helps the Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh close the wedding massacre chapter. Guddu, Golu and Dimpy who are still in hiding, reunite with a loyal partner and set their sights on Mirzapur.

episodes.title: VIKLAANG QUOTA
episodes.description: Akhandanand’s woes in the bedroom lead him to the doors of a sexologist. Beena continues to be gripped by the traumatic incident she endured but finds a compelling reason to survive. Guddu has to push himself to think beyond his physical strength while Golu has to learn the ropes of the trade. They make use of Dimpy’s past friendship and end up sending the Tripathis a strong message.

episodes.title: BHAYMUKT
episodes.description: Guddu and Golu are still not a threat to Akhandanand, but Munna thinks differently. Akhandanand assigns Munna to take charge of youth canvassing in the state along with the CM’s daughter, Madhuri Yadav. Beena safeguards a big secret. Guddu and Golu’s alliance with Lala begins to affect Akhandanand’s business. Golu decides to get Robin’s expertise. Sharad’s emotions overpower his thought process.

episodes.title: LANGDA
episodes.description: Akhandanand reprimands Munna and Sharad for their impulsive actions. Bablu’s diary becomes a key in learning secrets about the Tripathi family for Golu. In order to impress Akhandanand Tripathi, Sharad introduces him and Munna to one of Bihar’s most powerful business family, the Tyagis. A fortunate coincidence triggers an unexpected alliance between parties that have a common goal.

episodes.title: ANKUSH
episodes.description: There has been a huge setback in the Tripathi family’s business, Akhandanand smells a rat but uses this set back to his advantage. Munna is coerced in to taking a big step in his life which makes the Tripathis’ political alliances stronger. Ramakant is surprised to find an unexpected ally. Golu makes a business proposition to Shatrughan, but it falls through. The elections come to an end.

episodes.title: OOD BILAAV
episodes.description: Guddu and Golu are growing from strength to strength, Guddu strives to become the bahubali of Balia. On the personal front, Guddu is getting closer to Shabnam, who asks him to let go of the past. Shatrugan doesn’t have the same influence in his family as his elder brother, a fact that Golu notices and uses to her advantage. The wheels of a Adventuretic political coup are set in to motion.

episodes.title: CHAUCHAK
episodes.description: Sharad Shukla and JP Yadav successfully manage to dent Akhandanand’s political aspirations. JP Yadav then calls for a debauche celebration with Zarina in private. After suffering a significant personal loss, Guddu takes upon an unexpected responsibility and Shabnam agrees to help. Golu doesn’t take this too well as she feels Shabnam will come in the way of their larger objective.

episodes.title: BUTTERSCOTCH
episodes.description: Beena gives birth to a boy and is worried about the safety of the child. Lala is unhappy with Guddu’s closeness to Shabnam. Golu herself is in immense pain, questions what she has become. Maurya is frustrated with constant setbacks and decides to meet with the IG. Munna takes matters in his own hands when Maqbool’s lies are resurfaced. Loyalties are at stake as a repercussion of Munna’s actions.

episodes.title: KING OF MIRZAPUR
episodes.description: Beena confronts the horrors of her past, leaving the Tripathi household in chaos. Munna’s new found power through Madhuri leads him to make a drastic confrontation with Akhandanand. Dadda calls for a meeting with Mama, Shatrughan and Bharat. Ramakant is forced to confront his own beliefs. Guddu and Golu assure Beena of the promise they made. Sharad looks to bring his plan to a conclusion.

episodes.title: Tetua
episodes.description: While Ramakant is tried for the murder of SSP Maurya, Guddu and Golu's claim to the throne is questioned because Kaleen Bhaiya's body is missing. Madhuri vows to fulfill her father's mission of a crime free state.

episodes.title: Mexico
episodes.description: Guddu and Golu kickstart the business again, but are still looking for a supply of opium which would allow them to establish control over Purvanchal's underworld. In the hunt for the same control, Sharad tries to crack a deal with one of Guddu's old allies, while Madhuri tries to eliminate Guddu.

episodes.title: Pratishodh
episodes.description: Guddu cements his power over Mirzapur while Sharad finally makes a very strong ally. Golu receives a threat from Bharat. Ramakant turns down Robin's offer and faces danger in prison. Meanwhile Madhuri strategises to bring Guddu down in other ways.

episodes.title: Kekadaa
episodes.description: Ramakant's case is in danger with the appearance of a new witness. In an attempt to save her father's opium business from collapsing, Shabnam turns to Guddu for help. Meanwhile Golu gets some much awaited information about the still missing Kaleen Bhaiya.

episodes.title: Traahi
episodes.description: Golu plans an attack outside Mirzapur without Guddu. Guddu returns from Nepal to find Golu missing. Sharad senses something is amiss in Siwan and decides to shift his most guarded secret to Jaunpur.

episodes.title: Bhasmasur
episodes.description: Purvanchal is set ablaze with a gang war between Sharad and Guddu. Madhuri makes strong decisions to break the police-gangster nexus, while a ghost from the past resurfaces. Ramakant finds a purpose in prison, which catches Lala's attention.

episodes.title: Bum-pilaat
episodes.description: Purvanchal is thrown into turmoil following the shocking incident in the jail. Dadda confronts his son, while Sharad and Bharat have a fallout as well. A baithak is called to resolve the gang feud.

episodes.title: Raja Beta
episodes.description: Guddu goes down a dark downward spiral as he loses people close to him. A new judge is assigned before Ramakant's final hearing. Meanwhile, Saloni discovers her husband's secrets. IG Dubey is reinstated and is tasked with one mission: Capturing Guddu Pandit.

episodes.title: Ansh
episodes.description: Beena is compelled to find safety after the fall of Guddu. Madhuri urges Sharad to let go of the past for a better future. Will Shatrughan be able to convince Saloni to keep his secret? A broken Dimpy wants to take matters into her own hands.

episodes.title: Pratibimbh
episodes.description: Golu returns to Mirzapur only to discover the chaos that ensued in her absence. Madhuri inaugurates Aam Bagh despite the threat of JP Yadav looming large. As Dussehra closes in, there is only one question: Who will ascend the throne of Mirzapur?

episodes.title: Dharavi Main Bulaya Hai
episodes.description: Thalaivan has an empire worth Rs 30,000 crore in the heart of Mumbai’s Dharavi. CM Janvi Surve gets insecure about Thalaivan’s growing popularity and orders a police raid on this empire in order to threaten Thalaivan. Will the plan work? Can Thalaivan really be moved by such raids?

episodes.title: Thok Doonga Saale Ko
episodes.description: An officer of the JCP, Jayant Gavaskar decides to take on Thalaivan and makes it his mission to bring down him and his operations in Dharavi Bank. On the other hand, Thalaivan’s nephew- Mahesh comes to know about the news that is going to change the course of his life. What is the news? Will JCP Gavaskar succeed in his mission?

episodes.title: Veenu
episodes.description: Besides professional obligations, JCP Jayant Gavaskar also has personal motivations for hating Thalaivan and the past is revealed. Dharavi prepares to witness the big showdown. What lies ahead of the showdown? Will one of the two parties emerge victorious?

episodes.title: War Room
episodes.description: The leaks make Thalaivan furious and he is determined to find out who was behind the sabotage. Joe now has to prove his loyalty. JCP Gavaskar makes a big win and his war room is set in motion. Meanwhile, Mahesh and Sakeena meet. Will Thalaivan be able to find the source of the leak? What happens when he comes to know the truth?

episodes.title: Bhool Bhulaiya
episodes.description: JCP Gavaskar succeeds in attacking Thalaivan. But, can he take the man out of the maze of Dharavi? Will Thalaivan retaliate against the attack?

episodes.title: Family
episodes.description: In the latest development, a power struggle ensues between Thalaivan’s eldest son, Shiva and the rest of the family. Meanwhile, JCP Gavaskar and Jaanvi plan their next move. What are they planning to do?

episodes.title: Make Him Suffer
episodes.description: JCP Gavaskar becomes the new commissioner of Mumbai Police and the first agenda on his target is revenge. Though he remains unaware that a new sinister plan is brewing in the streets of Dharavi against him.

episodes.title: Withdrawal
episodes.description: The demands of people to close their accounts with Dharavi Bank grow louder and louder. At the same time, Micheal comes to know about Sakeena’s betrayal. How will he react to this? How will Thalaivan control the growing tension amidst the people?

episodes.title: Secrets
episodes.description: Shiva comes to know about the secret of his younger brother. Mahesh and Deepa decide to run away and leave the country. On the other hand, Thalaivan forges a new alliance and declares war on Gavaskar. How will Gavaskar respond?

episodes.title: Koi Bhi Nahi Bachega
episodes.description: How will the game end? Will Dharavi Bank really burn down? Who will be the culprit of the end of Dharavi Bank CM Janvi, commissioner Gavaskar or the mighty man himself- Thalaivan?

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: Hotel night manager Jonathan Pine receives a plea for help from a well-connected guest.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: On the Mediterranean island of Mallorca, Roper’s life of luxury and calm is shattered. Six months earlier, Burr continues her recruitment of Pine, sending him to Devon to build his cover story.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: While he continues to recuperate in Roper’s villa, Pine starts to dig up secrets about the other members of the household. Meanwhile, Burr and Steadman seize on an opportunity to recruit a new asset.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Roper welcomes Pine into his inner circle, leaving Corky out in the cold. Meanwhile, Burr has concerns for the safety of her source, when she suspects key information has been leaked to the River House.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: A suspicious Roper gathers his entourage around him in an attempt to root out the traitor, forcing Pine to play a dangerous game. In London, Burr and Steadman face mounting opposition from Whitehall.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Roper and his team return to Cairo for the deal, reuniting Pine with an old enemy. Pine risks it all to put his plan in motion. A discredited Burr makes one last stand.

episodes.title: Someone Has Betrayed
episodes.description: The life of Taj, a former boxing champion, is turned upside down after a failed assassination attempt on Colonel Joel of the French colonial army.

episodes.title: Under The Table
episodes.description: Nouran visits her ex-husband Taj to see their daughter Salma. Saleem offers Taj a risky mission. Later, Taj finds himself in a sticky situation after a gambling game.

episodes.title: The Suit
episodes.description: Struggling to find a way out of the financial bond dilemma, Taj reconsiders Saleem's offer.

episodes.title: In The Ring
episodes.description: Taj prepares to fight a Nazi boxer in the French barracks, putting in motion his and Saleem's plan to gain access to secret files on the informer.

episodes.title: The Archives
episodes.description: Following Syria's declaration of independence, Saleem tries talking Taj into giving their mission another shot.

episodes.title: The Allied Forces Are In Damascus
episodes.description: As Saleem attempts to hide the secret files in a secure location, Taj seeks Marion's assistance to rescue Subhi from the hospital.

episodes.title: In The Ministry Of Interior
episodes.description: Zakaria continues interrogating Saleem. Meanwhile, Taj tries to locate the files Saleem concealed before his arrest.

episodes.title: The German Airplane
episodes.description: Taj devises a plan to blackmail Zakaria into releasing Saleem from prison by taking compromising photos of him.

episodes.title: Jenny
episodes.description: Taj reveals to Saleem that Jenny stole the files. Colonel Joel pressures Zakaria to find out how Saleem managed to escape.

episodes.title: Little Secrets
episodes.description: Taj begins interrogating Jenny so he can get his hands on the secret files. Henry leaves the hospital with vengeance blazing in his eyes.

episodes.title: Artist
episodes.description: To save his beloved grandpa's printing press from going under, brilliant artist Sunny comes up with an ingenious but dangerous plan. A determined officer, Michael, corners his arch-nemesis, counterfeiting kingpin Mansoor Dalal.

episodes.title: Social Service
episodes.description: Sunny's plan works, but there is no end to greed. Michael tries to get an anti-counterfeiting task force sanctioned. Megha’s passion project has no takers among the powers that be.

episodes.title: CCFART
episodes.description: CCFART is formed. Sunny and Firoz accept a deal almost too large for them. Michael gate-crashes his son’s birthday party even though he is not invited. Michael hires Megha, but she steps on a few toes trying to track down the ‘artist’ who made the sandwich note.

episodes.title: Dhanrakshak
episodes.description: Dhanrakshak is launched, a huge victory for CCFART. Michael’s attempts to reconcile with his wife only push her further away. A rattled Sunny looks for his missing Grandpa, with no help from the inept bureaucracy. Mansoor’s operations are threatened by Dhanrakshak, and he needs a new note that can fool the new scanner.

episodes.title: Second Oldest Profession
episodes.description: Sunny cracks the Supernote. Michael gets a breakthrough in Bangladesh. Mansoor feels pressure from his bosses, and wants Sunny to take on a bigger role in his organisation. Megha finally finds someone she might be romantically interested in.

episodes.title: Cat and Mouse
episodes.description: Sunny has a mole in CCFART. Michael has a mole in Mansoor's organisation. Sunny adopts a risky plan, "Trojan Horse" to smuggle a huge shipment of notes to India.

episodes.title: Supernote
episodes.description: Sunny and Firoz love living the high life, as Sunny finds himself falling in love with Megha. Megha uncovers an important secret about the Supernote. Michael does something unorthodox to spur Minister Gahlot into action. Mansoor desperately needs to bring the cash into market.

episodes.title: Crash and Burn
episodes.description: A trap is laid! Sunny and Firoz almost get caught. Michael, not one to give up, has yet another plan! Mansoor's very existence is at stake. Megha is very close to uncovering a devastating truth. Sunny pays a price too heavy for his tryst with crime.

episodes.title: Missing
episodes.description: Homicide detective Om Singh is tasked with the case of media mogul Amar Roy's missing daughter. But he soon finds out that there is something more sinister at play.

episodes.title: Doubt
episodes.description: An unexpected lead cracks open a new dimension in the case. Om finds himself diving further into the mystery in order to solve it.

episodes.title: Loser
episodes.description: Om is caught in a web of lies and deception. As secrets buried underground threaten to resurface.

episodes.title: Silence
episodes.description: As the insidious plan enters its final phase, Om must choose whether to succumb to it or fight.

episodes.title: The Dead Never Lie
episodes.description: Sub Inspector Sanket Salelkar gets the first murder investigation of his career when Mala Coutinho, the owner of a 200-year-old Portuguese villa, is found murdered in her bed. The case looks pretty straightforward but his sister Sarla has other news for him.

episodes.title: To Be A Daughter
episodes.description: Sanket realizes he’s made a big career mistake and he has no idea how Mala Coutinho died, forget who killed her. Sanket enlists Sarla to help with the case and together they discover their first clue, a possible new murder weapon?

episodes.title: Echoes From The Past
episodes.description: The needle of suspicion turns to Mala’s daughter, Shalini. However, the truth is shrouded in different versions of the same incident. A new lead turns up with new information about Mala’s life but the cause of death remains elusive.

episodes.title: All That Glitters
episodes.description: Sanket discovers the true nature of Mala and Vishwas’s relationship even as Ignatius and Shalini continue to withhold information. A missing jewelry piece brings a new suspect and Sanket lays a trap hoping that the killer reveals themselves.

episodes.title: The Thin Line
episodes.description: Sarla’s past comes back to haunt her as Sanket’s trap yields a catch, but soon he realizes that he’s caught the wrong fish yet again. As he faces suspension, Sarla finally cracks the case and only to realise that it’s a perfect crime.

episodes.title: Hana and Mizuki
episodes.description: Hana's love of storytelling draws the attention of the Broadcasting Club's president, Mizuki, who tries to recruit her. However, Hana has reasons to decline her offer.

episodes.title: Interest and Talent
episodes.description: The new club members must take turns introducing one another, causing Hana to wonder what her strengths are.

episodes.title: Dreams and a Sleepover
episodes.description: Hana's enthusiasm deflates as Mr. Kichijoji readies the club for an upcoming competition. Why must she want to win? Why can't she just enjoy doing what she loves?

episodes.title: A First and a Friend
episodes.description: A spontaneous question causes Hana to freeze during her first broadcast. It's one thing to stick to the script. But improvising? That's a completely different story.

episodes.title: Blue Spring and an Umbrella
episodes.description: Anne is realistic, while Hana is idealistic; disagreements are inevitable. However, that won't stop Hana from trying to befriend her fellow club member.

episodes.title: Scripts and a Pancake
episodes.description: The club members decide on what category they will each compete in at the Kyoto NHK Cup preliminaries, recitation or announcing. Toga will not enter in either.

episodes.title: Big Sister and Little Brother
episodes.description: It’s a tight deadline, but the broadcasting club has the will to complete their submission to the original TV drama category.

episodes.title: Satisfaction and Unfinished
episodes.description: Shura is an expert storyteller, and her ability to conjure an entire city in her audience’s mind proves that Hana still has a long way to go.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: Anamika’s sudden disappearance launches an investigation. Flashes of the preceding weeks reveal her strained marriage and a troubling incident at home.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: As public concern for Anamika grows, Avi suspects Nikhil while Shobha distrusts Manish. Amara recalls Anamika’s concern over her acting aspirations.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Shobha questions Nikhil’s film financier. In flashbacks, truths emerge about Anamika’s wealth and Manish’s diagnosis. Anamika wonders what Avi is hiding.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Earlier weeks reveal Anamika's growing defiance and an altercation that leaves Avi distraught. In the present, Billy begins his own search for Anamika.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Shobha’s alarming discovery spawns more arguments within the family. In the past, pressure pushes Amara near a breaking point and Anamika faces danger.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: A visit to Manish’s farmhouse gives Anamika clarity. In the present day, amid news of a murder, a music launch for Anamika and Manish’s film turns tense.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: The police team rushes to track down the site of an alarming clue. Shobha urges Avi to tell her what he knows — and he lets damning family secrets spill.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: A sad development stokes public frenzy. While Shobha can't shake a gut feeling on Anamika's whereabouts, someone else knows more than they let on.
